daf = deepspeech_audio_features
from IPython.display import Audio, Image, display
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import soundfile as sf

def sigmoid(x):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-x))

def inv_sigmoid(x):
    return -np.log(1 / x - 1)

def change_mask_contrast(mask, m=1, b=0):
    return sigmoid(m * inv_sigmoid(mask) + b)

def show_masked_audio(name, m, b):
    mask = change_mask_contrast(np.load('experience-sentence-mask.npy'), m, b)
    audio, sr = sf.read('meeting-4-audio/experience.wav')
    filtered_audio_filename = 'meeting-4-audio/experience-sentence-filtered-%s.wav' % name
    sf.write(filtered_audio_filename,
             daf.apply_mask_to_audio(mask, audio, sr),
             sr)
    def printeq(s):
        print(s)
        print('\n' + len(s) * '=' + '\n')
    printeq('Transcription of masked MFCCs: "%s"' % daf.transcribe_mfccs(mask * \
        daf.audiofile_to_mfccs('meeting-4-audio/experience.wav')))
    titles = ['Transcription of original audio', 'Transcription of filtered audio']
    filenames = ['meeting-4-audio/experience.wav', filtered_audio_filename]
    for title, filename in zip(titles, filenames):
        display(Audio(filename))
        plt.plot(sf.read(filename)[0])
        plt.show()
        print(title + ': "' + daf.transcribe_audiofile(filename) + '"')
